            "answer_text": "Dear M Anonymous, To write the capital A in cursive, you have many choices. The sheet below is something I created to show a young friend how to write cursive properly with the start and end points marked. (His school isn\u2019t teaching cursive in class!) However, when I write cursive, I often add some flair, so I don\u2019t always use the \u201ccorrect\u201d way of writing letters. There\u2019s also the Palmer method of writing cursive. Hope this helps! Also see the excellent answer by Caleb Rothschild.  Below is a page from my bullet journal showing a cursive alphabet I wrote.  - Also see Sarah Madden's answer to How can someone who never learned cursive read it? \u2014Sarah M., posted 10 April 2018 (updated 16 September 2019)  QUESTION: What is the correct form of writing a capital \u201ca\u201d in cursive? (asked 31 March 2017) ",
