            "answer_text": "This is a correct \u2018A\u2019:  (Google Images) And, this is a correct \u2018A\u2019:  (Google Images) And this is also a correct \u2018A\u2019:  The truth is that there are dozens of forms of cursive ranging from the utilitarian styles like the Palmer style to the extremely ornate Spencerian and Copperplate styles. Now, while in many third-grade classrooms, the first \u2018A\u2019 may be considered technically correct, cursive is an incredibly expressive, individualistic art form that each person has. So, all of the above \u2018A\u2019s are correct\u2014unless it is a graded third-grade cursive assignment in which it most likely the first one. ",
